<h2><a name="tutho"></a>Technical Challenges of 3D Video Processing</h2>
<p><strong>Date/Time</strong>: July 11, Â morning 9:00 - 12:30</p>
<p><strong>Room</strong>: <a href="program.php#jhc">JHC.02</a></p>
<p><strong>Abstract</strong></p>
<p align="justify">In recent years, various three-dimensional video services have become available and the demand for three-dimensional video processing is growing rapidly. Since 3DTV is considered as the next generation  broadcasting service that can deliver realistic and immersive experiences by supporting user-friendly interactions, a number of advanced three-dimensional video technologies have been studied. In this tutorial lecture, after reviewing the current status of 3DTV research activities, we are going to cover several challenging issues of 3D video processing, such as camera calibration, image rectification, illumination  compensation and color correction. In this tutorial lecture, we are also going to discuss the MPEG activities for 3D video coding, including depth map estimation, prediction structure for multi-view video coding, multi-view video-plus-depth coding, and intermediate view synthesis at virtual viewpoints.</p>
